A towering crane in NYC toppled, crushing buildings and killing four.
The 19-story crane split, pulverizing a townhouse and damaging others.
Amid a construction boom, the collapse raised safety concerns.
Rescue crews searched for survivors in the rubble.
The tragic accident highlighted the risks of working with cranes in the city.
Despite efforts to stabilize the crane, it fell unexpectedly, causing devastation.
The incident sparked discussions about crane safety in densely populated areas.
The city mourned the loss of lives and reflected on the dangers of construction work.
